    <item>
      <title>1.0.3</title>
      <sparkle:version>137</sparkle:version>
      <sparkle:shortVersionString>1.0.3</sparkle:shortVersionString>
      <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.2</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
      <description><![CDATA[<p>A small reliability release for first-run setup.</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Clearer Screen Recording setup.</strong> When Hindsight is opened from outside your Applications folder &mdash; where macOS runs it from a temporary, locked-down copy &mdash; setup now tells you to move Hindsight to Applications and reopen it, which is the only way the Screen Recording permission will stick. Previously it pointed you at the &ldquo;+&rdquo; button, which can&rsquo;t take effect in that case.</li>
  <li><strong>Sturdier packaging.</strong> The disk image is now signed unambiguously, and the diagnostics behind the Screen Recording grant were tightened so first-run setup issues are easier to trace.</li>
</ul>
<p>No feature changes &mdash; everything in 1.0.0 is unchanged. Requires macOS 14.2 or later, Apple Silicon.</p>]]></description>
      <pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 06:58:39 +0000</pubDate>
